<p>Border tokens define the edges and corners of Web Awesome components. They use <code>rem</code> units so they scale with root font size. Scale multipliers let you uniformly adjust all border widths or radii at once.</p>

<h2>Border Style</h2>
<p>A single style token controls the line type used for all component borders throughout your theme.</p>

<table class="token-table wa-hover-rows">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Custom Property</th><th>Description</th><th>Preview</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr id="tok-wa-border-style">
      <td class="token-name"><code>--wa-border-style</code></td>
      <td>Standard border line style used across all components</td>
      <td><div class="swatch" style="border-style: var(--wa-border-style)"></div></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Border Width</h2>
<p>Border width tokens use <code>rem</code> units and are scaled by <code>--wa-border-width-scale</code>. Values below <code>1</code> make all borders thinner; values above <code>1</code> make them thicker.</p>

<table class="token-table wa-hover-rows">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Custom Property</th><th>Description</th><th>Preview</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr id="tok-wa-border-width-scale">
      <td class="token-name"><code>--wa-border-width-scale</code></td>
      <td>Global multiplier for all border width calculations</td>
      <td>—</td>
    </tr>
    <tr id="tok-wa-border-width-s">
      <td class="token-name"><code>--wa-border-width-s</code></td>
      <td>Thin border (1px), used for most component outlines</td>
      <td><div class="swatch" style="border-width: var(--wa-border-width-s)"></div></td>
    </tr>
    <tr id="tok-wa-border-width-m">
      <td class="token-name"><code>--wa-border-width-m</code></td>
      <td>Medium border (2px), used for emphasized borders</td>
      <td><div class="swatch" style="border-width: var(--wa-border-width-m)"></div></td>
    </tr>
    <tr id="tok-wa-border-width-l">
      <td class="token-name"><code>--wa-border-width-l</code></td>
      <td>Thick border (3px), used for prominent outlines</td>
      <td><div class="swatch" style="border-width: var(--wa-border-width-l)"></div></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Border Radius</h2>
<p>Border radius tokens control the corner rounding of Web Awesome components. Size-based tokens use <code>rem</code> units and scale with <code>--wa-border-radius-scale</code>. Values below <code>1</code> make corners sharper; values above <code>1</code> make them rounder. Shape tokens provide fixed shapes regardless of the scale.</p>

